---
// Fig 1 — the agent loop and where memory cuts cost. Monochrome, theme-aware
// via the site's CSS variables.
const { num = '1' } = Astro.props;
---
<figure class="fig">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 720 240" role="img" aria-label="Diagram of the agent loop: input feeds a repeated cycle of memory, plan, act, observe; the context grows every turn and memory is the only stage that can shrink it.">
    <defs>
      <marker id="arr" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M 0 1 L 9 5 L 0 9 z" fill="var(--muted)"></path>
      </marker>
    </defs>

    <!-- input -->
    <rect x="12" y="96" width="76" height="44" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="var(--line)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
    <text x="50" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="var(--ink)" font-weight="600">task</text>
    <line x1="88" y1="118" x2="128" y2="118" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"></line>

    <!-- loop container -->
    <rect x="132" y="28" width="416" height="184" rx="12" fill="none" stroke="var(--line)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="5 5"></rect>
    <text x="340" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" fill="var(--faint)" letter-spacing="1.5">REPEATED EVERY TURN</text>

    <!-- four stages -->
    <rect x="156" y="96" width="82" height="44" rx="8" fill="var(--ink)"></rect>
    <text x="197" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="var(--bg)" font-weight="600">memory</text>

    <rect x="262" y="96" width="70" height="44" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="var(--ink)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
    <text x="297" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="var(--ink)">plan</text>

    <rect x="356" y="96" width="70" height="44" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="var(--ink)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
    <text x="391" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="var(--ink)">act</text>

    <rect x="450" y="96" width="78" height="44" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="var(--ink)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
    <text x="489" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="var(--ink)">observe</text>

    <line x1="238" y1="118" x2="258" y2="118" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"></line>
    <line x1="332" y1="118" x2="352" y2="118" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"></line>
    <line x1="426" y1="118" x2="446" y2="118" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"></line>

    <!-- feedback arc: observe back to memory -->
    <path d="M 489 140 C 489 178, 197 178, 197 144" fill="none" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"></path>
    <text x="343" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="var(--muted)">every observation becomes next turn's input tokens</text>

    <!-- output -->
    <line x1="548" y1="118" x2="588" y2="118" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"></line>
    <rect x="592" y="96" width="116" height="44" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="var(--line)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
    <text x="650" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="var(--ink)" font-weight="600">answer</text>

    <!-- annotation on memory -->
    <path d="M 197 96 C 197 64, 240 56, 262 56" fill="none" stroke="var(--faint)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"></path>
    <text x="272" y="60" font-size="12" fill="var(--muted)">the only stage that can shrink what all the others pay for</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption><strong>Fig. {num}.</strong> The agent loop. Output of turn <em>n</em> becomes input cost of turn <em>n+1</em>; retries, redundant tool calls and long contexts all compound. Memory is the one component positioned to cut every term at once.</figcaption>
</figure>
